{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532575528,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwNzk2NDQ1MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-407964451"},"message":"@leo-yuriev","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1532597608,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODAzODAxMA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408038010"},"message":"Unfortunately here a lot of incompatibilities and inconsistencies with MSVC (and in general with other cases that differs from just the x86+gcc/mingw). \n\nBriefly, we should:\n1. Refactor cmake scripts to avoid checks and any if's for 32/64 and release/debug. This is required to support Ninja and othe multi-configuration generators.\n2. Avoid use features specific to gcc or provide extra marcos (line inside t1ha).\n3. Replase all \"#if __x86_64__\" to \"#if UINTPTR_MAX \u003e 0xffffFFFFul || ULONG_MAX \u003e 0xffffFFFFul\" or \"if defined(__x86_64__) || defined(__x86_64)...\" like https://github.com/leo-yuriev/t1ha/blob/40f1cc26ed2c3cf82e6bec8804e834fa9245ed26/t1ha.h#L221-L238\n\nSo, this is a huge refactoring with a lot of changes (that I plan do this in https://github.com/leo-yuriev/HashContest).","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532598163,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODA0MDYxNA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408040614"},"message":"* I don't care much for ninja, as it usually doesn't work with \u003c16GB free ram, and I have no \u003e=32GB machine. With cmake/make is builds fine on small laptops.\n* Splitting up 64/32bit checks against intel checks is ok for me, but is not urgent.\n* Maybe old autotools probes are just easier. cmake is getting messy.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1532598916,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODA0NDA5Ng==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408044096"},"message":"Nowadays Microsoft Visual Studio 2017 able directly open a CMake projects, and internally uses Ninja generator for this. So, if we wanna support MSVC, then we should use CMake with neatness for multi-configuration generators.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1532599517,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODA0NjgzMQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408046831"},"message":"Windows10+MSVC2017+CMake+Ninja works fine on may laptop with 8Gb of RAM (I use it time-to-time for testing builds under windows).","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"b44207c7257fea92a0b294d571df4928c49dc14f"},"timestamp":1532627041,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODE3NzkyOQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408177929"},"message":"While I'm sure this is an interesting discussion (I see no value in supporting MSVC and personally have no use for anything other than x64), my issue is very specific - I'd like to know what exactly happened in the part of the commit that replaces opt_cmetrohash64_1.c and why. My hope in contributing the cmetrohash etc implementations was that they would continue to work and remain comparable to the state-of-the-art in future. Now one is broken and, even if it were runnable, works entirely differently. Completely changing an implementation removing optimizations is hardly the right way to handle build issues, no?\n\nIn that particular respect, the solution is either to back out the change to opt_cmetrohash64_1.c and, if necessary for compatibility, ifdef cmetrohash64_1o out on anything besides gcc - or leave everything as is meaning in future I should maintain hash functions I care about outside the tree in my own fork.\n\n@leo-yuriev Можно ответить по-русски, если Вам так легче.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532627803,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODE4MDEzNQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408180135"},"message":"Full agree. First we need to restore opt_cmetrohash64_1.c and find a cfg where it's broken. \nOn the smokers and my machine it compiles fine.\nThen re-enable MSVC","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532627803,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDExMjg1OTE3OQ=="},"target":"158eb82288c2556ff280b1f57b1ad6e24da18f9a7b7728dc1e92fa93d7715dea","message":"Full agree. First we need to restore opt_cmetrohash64_1.c and find a cfg where it's broken. \nOn the smokers and all my x86_64 machines it compiles fine.\nThen re-enable MSVC","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532628091,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDExMjg2MDk4Nw=="},"target":"158eb82288c2556ff280b1f57b1ad6e24da18f9a7b7728dc1e92fa93d7715dea","message":"Full agree. First we need to restore opt_cmetrohash64_1.c and find a cfg where it's broken. \nOn the smokers and all my x86_64 machines it compiles fine. 32bit is broken.\nThen re-enable MSVC","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532628134,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDExMjg2MTI5MQ=="},"target":"158eb82288c2556ff280b1f57b1ad6e24da18f9a7b7728dc1e92fa93d7715dea","message":"Full agree. First we need to restore opt_cmetrohash64_1.c and find a cfg where it's broken. \nOn the smokers and all my x86_64 machines it compiles fine. 32bit is broken in jody_block_hash()\nThen re-enable MSVC","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532631261,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDExMjg4MzMwMA=="},"target":"158eb82288c2556ff280b1f57b1ad6e24da18f9a7b7728dc1e92fa93d7715dea","message":"Full agree. First we need to restore opt_cmetrohash64_1.c and find a cfg where it's broken. \nOn the smokers and all my x86_64 machines it compiles fine. 32bit is broken in jody_block_hash()\nThen re-enable MSVC. I've just added a windows smoker: https://ci.appveyor.com/project/rurban/smhasher/history","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532633959,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODIxMTkzNQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408211935"},"message":"@leo-yuriev How did you compile MSVC? I get siphash compilation errors: https://ci.appveyor.com/project/rurban/smhasher/build/0.2.10/job/fbqvb42nl6ybogv4\nVS15 is too old, so I use now VS17 MSVC 19.14.26433.0, which is fine.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532675746,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODMzMzU1NA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408333554"},"message":"32bit and msvc works now again: https://travis-ci.org/rurban/smhasher/builds\nhttps://ci.appveyor.com/project/rurban/smhasher/history\n\n@paulie-g: can you check master?","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"b44207c7257fea92a0b294d571df4928c49dc14f"},"timestamp":1532681214,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODM1NDQ4OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408354489"},"message":"I'm not sure what you'd like me to check - I don't have a Windows machine or MSVC. My complaint wasn't that the MSVC build was borked, but that a particular commit supposedly aimed at fixing the MSVC build included a change that overwrote opt_cmetrohash64_1.c for a reason I couldn't identify.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532684743,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODM2OTM4Ng==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408369386"},"message":"@paulie-g You said the MSVC fix complete broke opt_cmetrohash64_1.c, and I never got answer what exactly was broken.\nSo I found out by myself that MSVC and 32bit was broken, which I fixed.\n\nfe3f367e047a23ebdfe68 replaced your GNU \u0026\u0026computed_label extension with a proper switch statement, which is fine with me. computed labels are unportable, and on clang/gcc/icc -O3 it compiles to the same code, just switch adds a range check at the beginning.\nWe could re-add the computed labels in a huge ifdef, but it's not worth the effort IMHO.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"b44207c7257fea92a0b294d571df4928c49dc14f"},"timestamp":1532689484,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODM4NjkwMA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408386900"},"message":"It's broken as in you can't run it, `SMHasher cmetrohash64_1o` says there is no such hash.\n\nIt's an optimization. At least at the time, it was faster than a switch statement, which is why I ended up using it instead of a switch and two-three other things I tried. I vaguely remember the resulting assembly avoiding an unnecessary pipeline stall, but it's been 3 years. My point was that clobbering other people's work without discussion is a bit strange, especially with a commit that says 'msvc fixes'. If you'd done it, I couldn't complain - it's your project, but when another contributor does it without asking.. Since you've now said you're in favour, I consider the issue closed. It's really not worth me taking up your time since the only person who cares about this metrohash variant is me in all probability ;)","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"deab18ec55cc2ccf4a5b83e53e09884fe45c1f2c"},"timestamp":1532691249,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODM5Mjc3MA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408392770"},"message":"@paulie-g if your optimization was gcc-specific, then why you complain that other people replaced it with portable, even if slower, variant? I think the best you can do is to provide patch which conditionally compiles to gcc.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1532705770,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODQ1NjE5MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408456191"},"message":"@paulie-g, try https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/pull/47 for `cmetrohash64_1o`.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"b44207c7257fea92a0b294d571df4928c49dc14f"},"timestamp":1532722299,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODUyNjY4NA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408526684"},"message":"It really doesn't matter at this point. Having looked at the tests in @demerphq SMhasher, it is clear that metrohash-c itself is somehow different from metrohash-cpp and has additional quality problems. Therefore, my optimization has them as well. Recently added hashes like mum and @leo-yuriev 's t1ha appear to have both better quality and better/similar performance respectively. I'll need to test them more thoroughly and in-situ with real-world data, but the chances are either one or both obsolete metrohash for my use case.","files":null},{"type":4,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532788465,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDExOkNsb3NlZEV2ZW50MTc1ODU1NjkzMQ=="},"status":2},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1532788526,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwODYxMjAxMQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/45#issuecomment-408612011"},"message":"Re-enabled on 32bit with  862a519","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"cf2dfd8ada60f9130df8